<common-name datatype='string'>yjbEFGH</common-name>
<comment datatype='string'>The &lt;i&gt;yjbEFGH&lt;/i&gt; operon was previously shown to be involved in exopolysaccharide synthesis [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17379715&quot;&gt;Ferrieres07&lt;/a&gt;], biofilm formation, and the Rcs phosphorelay system [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/14651646&quot;&gt;Ferrieres03&lt;/a&gt;]. It is induced by osmotic stress [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12024246&quot;&gt;Rozen01&lt;/a&gt;] and is under positive control of the RpoS-regulated general stress response of &lt;i&gt;E. coli&lt;/i&gt; [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15184550&quot;&gt;Ihssen04&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15716429&quot;&gt;Weber05&lt;/a&gt;]. Nevertheless, it has been shown that RpoS has a negative and indirect effect on it [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17957352&quot;&gt;Ionescu08&lt;/a&gt;]. 
&lt;p&gt;
Induction of &lt;i&gt;yjbEFGH&lt;/i&gt; is restricted to relatively low cell densities and is positively affected by slow growth rates and a high oxygen concentration [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17957352&quot;&gt;Ionescu08&lt;/a&gt;].
&lt;p&gt;
The expression of the operon &lt;i&gt;yjbEFGH&lt;/i&gt; is increased when colicin (at 30 ng/ml) is added to the medium [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23421615&quot;&gt;Kamensek13&lt;/a&gt;].</comment>
